# Enforce LF line endings for all text files to prevent CRLF issues on Windows.
# Truss compares generated blocks byte-for-byte (BL-02); mixed line endings
# would cause false drift warnings.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicitly mark generated/managed Markdown as text (belt-and-suspenders).
*.md text eol=lf

# Binary files — never touch line endings.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
